fishdata <- fishdata1 %>%
  select(-c(Other, Replacement, `Patch note`, Transparency, `ID note`, `Behaviour note`)) %>%
  mutate(
    Date = dmy(Date),
  ) %>%
  mutate_at(
    c(2:5),
    ~ replace_na(., "empty")
  ) %>%
  mutate_at(c(2:5), ~ factor(.)) %>%
  filter(Family != "Apogonidae")

2.2 EDA

  1. Algae EDA
algae.sum <- algaedata %>%
  group_by(Treatment) %>%
  summarise(
    mean.len = mean(Length),
    n.thalli = length(Replicate),
    SE.len = sd(Length) / sqrt(length(Replicate)),
    mean.wt = mean(Weight),
    SE.wt = sd(Weight) / sqrt(length(Replicate)),
  )


algaedata %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Replicate) %>%
  summarise(plot.weight = sum(Weight)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(Treatment) %>%
  summarise(
    mean.plot.wt = mean(plot.weight),
    SE.plot.wt = (sd(plot.weight) / sqrt(5))
  ) %>%
  left_join(algae.sum, .) -> algae.sum

algae.sum <- mutate(algae.sum, )

algae.sum %>% view()


g.len <- ggplot(algaedata) +
  aes(y = Length, x = Treatment) +
  geom_point(alpha = 0.1) +
  geom_violin(fill = NA) +
  labs(y = "Length (cm)") +
  theme(
    family = "calibri", text = element_text(size = 8, color = "black"),
    axis.text = element_text(size = 10),
    axis.title = element_text(size = 12),
  ) +
  theme_bw()

A bit of an outlier in Length - One plot (W5) had an extra long 52cm thallus. I checked in the video and this was not a typo. However its weight was not super high (70g). Lengths otherwise fairly similar, around 30cm

Weights per plot: BQ < DL <= BH <= DM < W

  1. Fish EDA
fish.sum <- fishdata %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Replicate, Date) %>%
  summarise(abundance = sum(count)) %>%
  ungroup() %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Replicate) %>%
  summarise(
    mean.abnd = mean(abundance),
    se.abnd = sd(abundance) / sqrt(length(abundance))
  )

g.sp.richness <- fishdata %>%
  group_by(Treatment, Replicate, Date) %>%
  summarise(
    sp.richness = if_else(Species != "empty",
      true = length(unique(Species)),
      false = 0
    )
  ) %>%
  ggplot() +
